        <heading>1768.  Swearing of jurors; selection of foreman</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1768.  Swearing of jurors; selection of foreman
When the jury has been accepted by all parties, the jurors shall be sworn to try the case in a just and impartial manner, to the best of their judgment, and to render a verdict according to the law and the evidence.  When the jury has retired, the jurors shall select a foreman to preside over them and sign the verdict which they may render.</p>
        </content>
